      Set the gear ratio of the drivetrain.

      The gear ratio is the ratio of the motor's rotational speed to the wheel's linear speed. This value should be set to the gear ratio of the drivetrain.

    • withInvertLeftSide

      public DrivetrainConfig.DrivetrainConfigBuilder withInvertLeftSide(boolean invertLeftSide)
      Set whether the left side of the drivetrain should be inverted.

      Inverting a side of the drivetrain means that the motor will turn in the opposite direction when given a positive output. This can be useful for drivetrains that have their motors mounted in a way that causes them to naturally turn in the opposite direction.

      Parameters:
      invertLeftSide - whether the left side should be inverted
